# README Rules

Create README files that are clear, technical, concise and useful for developers or recruiters reviewing the project.

## Tone

Use:
- clean technical language
- concise explanations
- practical engineering wording

Avoid:
- excessive emojis
- hype words
- fake enterprise claims
- “revolutionary”, “innovative”, “cutting-edge”
- generic AI marketing language
- badge overload

## Process

Before writing README content, analyze:
- repository structure
- backend routes
- frontend structure
- Dockerfile / docker-compose
- requirements.txt / pyproject.toml
- package.json
- database usage
- environment variables
- deployment config

Do not invent features.

## Recommended structure

Use when appropriate:

```md
# Project Name

Short description.

## Live Demo

## Features

## Tech Stack

## Architecture

## Local Development

## Environment Variables

## Deployment

## Screenshots

## Future Improvements